==English==

===Noun Phrase===
'''shotgun shack'''

# (''colloquial'') A house with no internal barrier between the front and back doors.

===Quotations===

'''2004:'''  ''Familiar in working-class neighborhoods all over the South, the “shotgun” name reflects the fact a bullet fired at the front door could pass right out the back door, travelling the full length of the narrow house without ever encoutering any obstructions.'' &mdash; Duncan Spencer in [http://www.hillnews.com/issues/091102/hillscape.shtm The Hill, November 8, 2004]